<TITLE> BSF, BDR trade praise </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 1 (bdnews24.com)India has praised Bangladesh for the commitment to not allow its territory used against Indian interests. Bangladesh also thanked India for maintaining peace in the border during the BDR mutiny. At the end of a three-day meeting between border guards of the two next-door neighbours, BDR and the BSF in New Delhi, the two countries vowed to strengthen efforts to prevent trans-border crimes. The 29th director-general-level meeting between Bangladesh Rifles (BDR) and Border Security Force (BSF) ended Wednesday in New Delhi . BDR's director general Major General Mainul Islam and his Indian counterpart M L Kumawat led the delegations to the talks. "The DG BSF appreciated the commitment of the government of Bangladesh not to allow Bangladesh territory for any activity inimical to India," said a statement issued by the Indian high commission in Dhaka. The statement said both sides agreed to strengthen security cooperation. "The DG BDR expressed his gratitude for India's support and cooperation during the recent crisis. "He complemented BSF for their professional role in maintaining peace and tranquillity on Indo-Bangladesh border during the crisis (killing of army officers by the BDR mutineers)," it said. The meeting expressed "deepest condolences" for the killing of army officers. The issue of taking over work on maintenance of boundary pillars by BSF and BDR on the border which has been under discussion for sometime also figured during the conference, it said.
